  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Manage flooding in a Nicaraguan elementary school</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In a rural and impoverished Nicaraguan community, 200 young students are without the privilege of a reliable elementary education. Unsafe and unsanitary conditions caused by rainfall and flooding force them to frequently miss school, when they need to be learning fundamentals such as reading, writing, and basic math. EWB-PSU will manage this flooding with a long-term and low-maintenance stormwater infiltration system that is enthusiastically supported by the community members.</narrative>
  </description>
